  </meta>
  <preamble>At a duly called meeting of the Council of San Ildefonso Pueblo on the 22nd day of June, 2022, the following law was adopted:</preamble>
  <recitals>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>many employers have adopted a minimum wage of $15 per hour for full-time employees; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>the cost of living expenses including but not limited to rent, gasoline, food and etc. have significantly increased; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS,</conjunction>
      <text>in order to be competitive and provide employees with a sufficient rate of pay, the Council has determined that it is the Pueblo's best interest to establish a standard minimum wage of $15 per hour for full-time employees.</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>NOW THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED</conjunction>
      <text>that the Council hereby enacts the attached law entitled "MINIMUM WAGE ACT OF 2022."</text>
    </recital>
  </recitals>
